    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="20" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Central America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">El Paso, Tex.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 8, 1890</date>.
                            (Received July 10.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Mizner reports that serious troubles between the Government of Guatemala
                        and Salvadorian provisional leaders exist; that armies of 10,000 are
                        prepared for battle in either state, and that the presence of a United
                        States naval vessel on the Pacific coast of Central America is necessary for
                        the protection of our interests in those states.</p>
            </div>
